<title>HONG KONG: Bank of Communications sets $40 mln FRCD.</title>
<headline>Bank of Communications sets $40 mln FRCD.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following issue was announced by bookrunner ABN AMRO Bank.</p>
<p> BORROWER   PHILIPPINE BANK OF COMMUNICATIONS</p>
<p> AMOUNT     US$40 MLN  COUPON     3ML+87 BP  MATURITY  3 YRS</p>
<p> TYPE	 FRCD	 ISS PRICE  PAR	  LAUNCH    01.APR.97</p>
<p> PUTS	 ANNUAL     CALLS	ANNUAL     REPLIES   22.APR.97</p>
<p> LISTING    NONE	 REPAYMENT  BULLET     DENOMS    --</p>
<p> RATING     NONE	 SALE LMTS  CUSTOMARY  TAX PROV  --</p>
<p> NEG PLG    YES	  CRS DEF    YES	  FORCE MAJ IPMA2</p>
<p> HOME CTRY  PHILIPPINE GOV LAW    ENGLISH</p>
<p> PAY DATE   14.MAY.97 (EXPECTED)</p>
<p> MGT LEVELS AND FEES</p>
<p>   CO-LEAD MANAGERS   US$4 MLN+   23BP   ALL-IN  110</p>
<p>   CO-MANAGERS	  US$2 MLN+   18BP   ALL-IN  105</p>
<p> ARRANGER	ABN AMRO BANK (BOOKS)</p>
<p> CO-ARRANGER   WEST MERCHANT BANK</p>
<p> NOTES    DEBUT ISSUE FOR THE BANK. THE ISSUER IS THE 15TH</p>
<p>	    LARGEST BANK IN THE PHILIPPINES IN TERMS OF ASSETS.</p>
<p>--Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6960</p>
